03:47:57.447 --> 03:48:04.203
<i>Not much.
Above all, they were dishonest.</i>


1893
03:48:06.456 --> 03:48:10.793
<i>Was life in Grabow more fun
when the Jews were here?</i>


1894
03:48:24.891 --> 03:48:27.060
He'd rather not say.

1895
03:48:27.769 --> 03:48:29.979
Why does he call them dishonest?

1896
03:48:40.782 --> 03:48:44.410
They exploited the Poles.
That's what they lived off.


1897
03:48:44.494 --> 03:48:46.496
How did they exploit them?

1898
03:49:01.344 --> 03:49:03.221
By imposing their prices.

1899
03:49:08.142 --> 03:49:10.228
Ask her if she likes her house.

1900
03:49:11.854 --> 03:49:12.855
Yes,

1901
03:49:14.023 --> 03:49:17.068
but her children live
in much better houses.


1902
03:49:17.860 --> 03:49:19.862
In modern houses!

1903
03:49:22.990 --> 03:49:25.451
They've all gone to college.

1904
03:49:25.535 --> 03:49:29.038
Great! That's progress!

1905
03:49:33.376 --> 03:49:38.339
Her children are
the best educated in the village.


1906
03:49:38.422 --> 03:49:41.717
Very good, Madam!
Long live education!


1907
03:49:44.804 --> 03:49:48.558
Isn't this a very old house?

1908
03:49:51.060 --> 03:49:53.020
Yes, Jews lived here before.

1909
03:49:53.104 --> 03:49:56.607
So Jews used to live here.
Did she know them?


1910
03:49:59.402 --> 03:50:00.653
Yes.

1911
03:50:00.736 --> 03:50:02.572
What was their name?

1912
03:50:08.578 --> 03:50:09.579
She doesn't know.

1913
03:50:09.662 --> 03:50:11.998
What was their trade?

1914
03:50:13.207 --> 03:50:16.169
Benkel, their name was.

1915
03:50:17.587 --> 03:50:19.755
And what was their trade?

1916
03:50:27.889 --> 03:50:29.932
They had a butcher shop.

1917
03:50:30.725 --> 03:50:33.144
A butcher shop.
Why is she laughing?


1918
03:50:35.938 --> 03:50:39.400
Because the gentleman said it was...

1919
03:50:40.776 --> 03:50:44.614
a butcher shop where
you could buy cheap meat. Beef!


1920
03:50:46.073 --> 03:50:49.285
What does he think about
them being gassed in trucks?


1921
03:50:58.419 --> 03:51:00.963
He says he doesn't like that at all.

1922
03:51:10.514 --> 03:51:14.602
If they'd gone to Israel
of their own free will,


1923
03:51:14.685 --> 03:51:16.229
he might have been glad.

1924
03:51:16.312 --> 03:51:20.107
But killing them was unpleasant.

1925
03:51:23.319 --> 03:51:25.404
Does he miss the Jews?

1926
03:51:37.291 --> 03:51:40.628
Yes, because there were
some beautiful Jewesses.


1927
03:51:40.711 --> 03:51:42.755
For the young, it was... fine.

1928
03:51:42.838 --> 03:51:47.885
Are they sorry the Jews
are no longer here or pleased?


1929
03:51:56.435 --> 03:52:01.232
How can I tell?
I never went to school.


1930
03:52:01.524 --> 03:52:05.736
I can only think of how I am now.
Now I'm fine.


1931
03:52:06.570 --> 03:52:08.531
Is she better off?

1932
03:52:15.246 --> 03:52:17.832
Before the war, she picked potatoes.

1933
03:52:17.915 --> 03:52:21.669
Now she sells eggs,
and she's much better off.


1934
03:52:21.752 --> 03:52:25.423
Because the Jews are gone
or because of socialism?


1935
03:52:31.220 --> 03:52:35.975
She doesn't care, she's happy
because she's doing well now.


1936
03:52:36.058 --> 03:52:40.062
How did he feel about
losing his classmates?


1937
03:52:48.237 --> 03:52:50.156
It still upsets him.

1938
03:52:51.073 --> 03:52:52.908
Does he miss the Jews?

1939
03:52:54.243 --> 03:52:55.202
Certainly.

1940
03:52:55.286 --> 03:52:57.705
They were good Jews, Madam says.

1941
03:53:00.041 --> 03:53:03.586
GRABOW IN WINTER

1942
03:53:49.423 --> 03:53:52.635
<i>The Jews came in trucks,</i>

1943
03:53:54.762 --> 03:53:58.682
<i>and later there was
a narrow-gauge railway</i>


1944
03:53:58.766 --> 03:54:01.310
<i>that they arrived on.</i>

1945
03:54:02.478 --> 03:54:07.191
<i>They were packed tightly in the trucks,</i>

1946
03:54:07.274 --> 03:54:10.986
<i>or in the cars
of the narrow-gauge railway.</i>


1947
03:54:12.321 --> 03:54:14.615
Lots of women and children.

1948
03:54:14.949 --> 03:54:18.452
Men too, but most of them were old.

1949
03:54:18.661 --> 03:54:23.374
The strongest were put in work details.

1950
03:54:23.833 --> 03:54:28.045
They walked with chains on their legs.

1951
03:54:28.129 --> 03:54:31.215
In the morning, they fetched water,

1952
03:54:31.298 --> 03:54:34.593
looked for food, and so on.

1953
03:54:36.137 --> 03:54:39.265
These weren't killed right away.

1954
03:54:39.348 --> 03:54:41.434
That was done later.

1955
03:54:41.517 --> 03:54:44.520
I don't know what became of them.

1956
03:54:44.728 --> 03:54:47.314
They didn't survive, anyway.

1957
03:54:47.398 --> 03:54:49.692
Two of them did.

1958
03:54:49.775 --> 03:54:51.444
Only two.

1959
03:54:51.777 --> 03:54:53.779
They were in chains?

1960
03:54:54.822 --> 03:54:56.824
- On the legs.
- All of them?


1961
03:54:56.907 --> 03:55:04.123
The workers, yes.
The others were killed at once.


1962
03:55:04.206 --> 03:55:09.462
The Jewish work squad
went through the village in chains.


1963
03:55:09.795 --> 03:55:11.422
Yes.

1964
03:55:13.007 --> 03:55:15.676
Could people speak to them?

1965
03:55:15.759 --> 03:55:20.139
No, that was impossible.

1966
03:55:20.222 --> 03:55:21.599
Why?

1967
03:55:22.641 --> 03:55:24.685
No one dared.

1968
03:55:25.394 --> 03:55:28.022
- What?
- No one dared.


1969
03:55:28.564 --> 03:55:30.274
Understand?

1970
03:55:30.900 --> 03:55:32.985
Yes... No one dared.

1971
03:55:33.068 --> 03:55:35.070
Why, was it dangerous?

1972
03:55:35.154 --> 03:55:42.244
Yes, there were guards.

1973
03:55:45.289 --> 03:55:48.959
Anyway, people wanted
nothing to do with all that.


1974
03:55:49.960 --> 03:55:51.420
Do you see?

1975
03:55:51.504 --> 03:55:55.758
Gets on your nerves,
seeing that every day.


1976
03:56:03.349 --> 03:56:08.145
<i>You can't force a whole village
to watch such distress.</i>


1977
03:56:09.647 --> 03:56:11.982
<i>When the Jews arrived,</i>

1978
03:56:12.066 --> 03:56:16.028
<i>when they were pushed
into the church or the castle...</i>


1979
03:56:16.779 --> 03:56:18.614
<i>And the screams!</i>

1980
03:56:18.697 --> 03:56:22.326
<i>It was frightful!
Depressing.</i>


1981
03:56:22.576 --> 03:56:26.622
<i>Day after day, the same spectacle!</i>

1982
03:56:30.584 --> 03:56:34.797
<i>It was terrible!
A sad spectacle!</i>


1983
03:56:35.673 --> 03:56:39.301
<i>They screamed.
They knew what was happening.</i>


1984
03:56:40.636 --> 03:56:44.723
<i>At first, the Jews thought
they were going to be deloused.</i>


1985
03:56:45.266 --> 03:56:48.936
<i>But they soon understood.</i>

1986
03:56:49.019 --> 03:56:51.814
<i>Their screams grew wilder and wilder.</i>

1987
03:56:53.649 --> 03:56:56.694
<i>Horrifying screams. 
Screams of terror.</i>

1988
03:56:56.777 --> 03:57:00.573
<i>Because they knew
what was happening to them.</i>


1989
03:57:03.325 --> 03:57:07.496
<i>Do you know how many Jews
were exterminated there?</i>


1990
03:57:09.331 --> 03:57:13.210
<i>Four something,

1991
03:57:13.294 --> 03:57:14.878
400, 000.

1992
03:57:16.130 --> 03:57:20.009
<i>400,000, yes.
I knew it had a 4 in it.</i>


1993
03:57:21.385 --> 03:57:23.929
<i>Sad, sad, sad!</i>

1994
03:57:26.140 --> 03:57:29.226
<i>When the soldiers march,</i>

1995
03:57:29.310 --> 03:57:32.855
<i>the girls open
their windows and doors...</i>


1996
03:57:41.196 --> 03:57:47.077
<i>Do you remember
a Jewish child, a boy of 13?</i>


1997
03:57:47.328 --> 03:57:50.205
<i>He was in the work squad.</i>

1998
03:57:50.581 --> 03:57:53.709
<i>He sang on the river.</i>

1999
03:57:53.792 --> 03:57:55.878
- <i>On the Narew River?</i>
- <i>Yes.</i>


2000
03:57:56.712 --> 03:57:59.048
- <i>Is he still alive ?</i>
- <i>Yes, he is alive.</i>


2001
03:57:59.632 --> 03:58:04.094
<i>He sang a German song</i>

2002
03:58:04.553 --> 03:58:09.975
<i>that the SS in Chelmno taught him.</i>

2003
03:58:10.059 --> 03:58:13.103
<i>“When the soldiers march,</i>

2004
03:58:13.187 --> 03:58:15.648
<i>the girls open
their windows and doors...”</i>


2005
03:58:30.245 --> 03:58:32.498
SIMON SREBNIK,

2006
03:58:32.790 --> 03:58:36.752
the survivor of the 2nd period
of extermination at Chelmno


2007
03:58:37.086 --> 03:58:39.588
(the church period)

2008
03:59:50.075 --> 03:59:52.369
So it's a holiday in Chelmno!

2009
03:59:55.706 --> 03:59:58.041
What holiday?
What's being celebrated?


2010
04:00:03.088 --> 04:00:06.884
The birth of the Virgin Mary.
It's her birthday.


2011
04:00:09.136 --> 04:00:11.513
It's a huge crowd, isn't it?

2012
04:00:17.853 --> 04:00:21.356
But the weather's bad...
it's raining.


2013
04:00:22.024 --> 04:00:25.235
Ask them if they're glad
to see Srebnik again.


2014
04:00:29.990 --> 04:00:31.617
Very. it's a great pleasure.

2015
04:00:31.700 --> 04:00:33.160
Why?

2016
04:00:37.414 --> 04:00:40.626
They're glad to see him again,

2017
04:00:43.253 --> 04:00:46.298
because they know
all he's lived through.


2018
04:00:46.381 --> 04:00:50.260
Seeing him as he is now,
they're very pleased.


2019
04:00:50.344 --> 04:00:52.054
They're pleased?

2020
04:00:52.846 --> 04:00:55.557
Why does the whole village
remember him?


2021
04:01:11.073 --> 04:01:13.534
They remember him well

2022
04:01:14.743 --> 04:01:18.831
because he walked
with chains on his ankles,


2023
04:01:18.914 --> 04:01:22.709
and he sang on the river.

2024
04:01:22.918 --> 04:01:24.628
He was young,

2025
04:01:25.254 --> 04:01:27.130
he was skinny,

2026
04:01:27.673 --> 04:01:31.260
he looked ready for his coffin.

2027
04:01:31.343 --> 04:01:34.304
Ripe for a coffin!

2028
04:01:34.388 --> 04:01:36.682
Did he seem happy or sad?

2029
04:01:45.774 --> 04:01:47.818
Even the lady,

2030
04:01:57.411 --> 04:02:00.956
when she saw that child,

2031
04:02:01.039 --> 04:02:04.543
she told the German,
“Let that child go!”


2032
04:02:04.626 --> 04:02:06.712
He asked her, “Where to?”

2033
04:02:06.795 --> 04:02:08.422
“To his father and mother.”

2034
04:02:08.505 --> 04:02:12.301
Looking at the sky, he said,
“He'll soon go to them.”


2035
04:02:12.384 --> 04:02:14.303
The German said that?

2036
04:02:15.304 --> 04:02:19.141
They remember when the Jews
were locked in this church?


2037
04:02:23.896 --> 04:02:25.689
Yes, they do.

2038
04:02:30.193 --> 04:02:32.446
They brought them
to the church in trucks.


2039
04:02:32.529 --> 04:02:34.698
At what time of day?

2040
04:02:40.370 --> 04:02:42.164
All day long and into the night.

2041
04:02:42.414 --> 04:02:46.710
What happened?
Can they describe it in detail?


2042
04:03:05.854 --> 04:03:08.774
At first, the Jews
were taken to the castle.


2043
04:03:08.857 --> 04:03:12.277
Only later were they put
into the church.


2044
04:03:12.361 --> 04:03:14.529
The second phase, right!

2045
04:03:15.405 --> 04:03:18.450
In the morning,
they were taken into the woods.


2046
04:03:18.533 --> 04:03:22.371
How were they taken into the woods?

2047
04:03:28.961 --> 04:03:31.713
In very big armored vans.

2048
04:03:41.682 --> 04:03:44.434
The gas came through the bottom.

2049
04:03:47.521 --> 04:03:50.816
Then they were carried
in gas vans, right?


2050
04:03:54.403 --> 04:03:56.321
Yes, in gas vans.

2051
04:03:57.531 --> 04:03:59.950
Where did the vans pick them up?

2052
04:04:00.951 --> 04:04:02.703
- The Jews?
- Yes.


2053
04:04:06.081 --> 04:04:08.000
Here, at the church door.

2054
04:04:08.083 --> 04:04:10.752
The trucks pulled up where they are now?

2055
04:04:12.129 --> 04:04:14.172
No, they went right to the door.

2056
04:04:14.256 --> 04:04:17.592
The vans came to the church door?

2057
04:04:19.886 --> 04:04:24.307
And they all knew these were death vans?

2058
04:04:30.939 --> 04:04:33.191
Yes, they couldn't help knowing.

2059
04:04:35.152 --> 04:04:37.738
They heard screams at night?

2060
04:04:42.784 --> 04:04:44.995
The Jews moaned, they were hungry.

2061
04:04:47.873 --> 04:04:49.958
They were shut in and starved.

2062
04:04:50.167 --> 04:04:52.127
Did they have any food?

2063
04:04:58.717 --> 04:05:03.138
You couldn't look there.
You couldn't talk to a Jew.


2064
04:05:10.145 --> 04:05:14.524
Even going by on the road,
you couldn't look there.


2065
04:05:14.608 --> 04:05:16.651
Did they look anyway?

2066
04:05:22.491 --> 04:05:25.494
Yes, vans came,

2067
04:05:25.702 --> 04:05:28.747
and the Jews were moved farther off.

2068
04:05:28.830 --> 04:05:30.832
You could see them, but on the sly.

2069
04:05:30.916 --> 04:05:33.293
- In sidelong glances.
- That's right.


2070
04:05:37.339 --> 04:05:40.217
That's right, in sidelong glances.

2071
04:05:41.051 --> 04:05:44.513
What kind of cries and moans
were heard at night?


2072
04:06:01.738 --> 04:06:05.450
They called on Jesus and Mary and God,

2073
04:06:05.534 --> 04:06:08.203
sometimes in German, as she puts it.

2074
04:06:10.580 --> 04:06:13.667
The Jews called on Jesus, Mary and God!

2075
04:06:17.838 --> 04:06:22.467
The presbytery was full of suitcases.

2076
04:06:22.551 --> 04:06:24.553
The Jews' suitcases?

2077
04:06:26.221 --> 04:06:29.266
Yes, and there was gold.

2078
04:06:32.435 --> 04:06:35.647
How does she know there was gold?

2079
04:06:42.654 --> 04:06:45.866
The procession! <i>We'll</i> stop now.

2080
04:09:25.150 --> 04:09:27.277
Were there as many Jews
in the church


2081
04:09:27.360 --> 04:09:29.821
as there were Christians today?

2082
04:09:38.038 --> 04:09:39.331
Almost.

2083
04:09:39.414 --> 04:09:43.126
How many gas vans
were needed to empty it out?


2084
04:09:53.762 --> 04:09:55.263
An average of 50.

2085
04:09:55.347 --> 04:09:57.891
It took 50 vans to empty it!

2086
04:09:58.767 --> 04:10:00.894
In a steady stream?

2087
04:10:04.606 --> 04:10:05.398
Yes.

2088
04:10:05.482 --> 04:10:07.400
The lady said before

2089
04:10:07.484 --> 04:10:11.613
that the Jews' suitcases
were dumped in the house opposite.


2090
04:10:15.033 --> 04:10:17.577
What was in this baggage?

2091
04:10:22.082 --> 04:10:25.543
Pots with false bottoms.

2092
04:10:25.794 --> 04:10:30.256
What was in the false bottoms?

2093
04:10:35.136 --> 04:10:37.764
Valuables... objects of value.

2094
04:10:40.100 --> 04:10:43.937
They also had gold in their clothes.

2095
04:10:48.066 --> 04:10:52.529
When given food, the Jews
sometimes threw them valuables


2096
04:10:52.612 --> 04:10:54.406
or sometimes money.

2097
04:10:55.073 --> 04:10:59.369
They said before
it was forbidden to talk to Jews.


2098
04:11:05.834 --> 04:11:08.044
Absolutely forbidden.

2099
04:11:11.256 --> 04:11:13.716
Ask them if they miss the Jews.

2100
04:11:20.515 --> 04:11:22.225
Of course.

2101
04:11:25.019 --> 04:11:28.857
We wept too, Madam says.

2102
04:11:32.193 --> 04:11:36.197
And Mr. Kantarowski
gave them bread and cucumbers.


2103
04:11:45.373 --> 04:11:49.377
Why do they think
all this happened to the Jews?


2104
04:11:56.801 --> 04:11:59.220
Because they were the richest!

2105
04:12:00.930 --> 04:12:05.810
Many Poles were also exterminated.

2106
04:12:05.894 --> 04:12:07.395
Even priests.

2107
04:12:07.479 --> 04:12:09.355
Mr. Kantarowski...

2108
04:12:15.028 --> 04:12:17.739
will tell us what a friend told him.

2109
04:12:17.822 --> 04:12:20.742
It happened in Myndjewyce, near Warsaw.

2110
04:12:20.825 --> 04:12:22.285
Go on.

2111
04:12:40.428 --> 04:12:44.641
The Jews were gathered in a square.

2112
04:12:44.891 --> 04:12:48.937
The rabbi asked an SS man,
“Can I talk to them?”


2113
04:12:49.395 --> 04:12:51.439
The guard said yes.

2114
04:13:04.953 --> 04:13:09.707
So the rabbi said
that around 2,000 years ago,


2115
04:13:09.791 --> 04:13:14.295
the Jews condemned
the innocent Christ to death.


2116
04:13:25.473 --> 04:13:28.893
And when they did that,
they cried out,


2117
04:13:28.977 --> 04:13:33.273
“Let his blood fall on our heads
and on our sons' heads.”


2118
04:13:47.453 --> 04:13:51.165
Then the rabbi told them,

2119
04:13:51.249 --> 04:13:56.671
“Perhaps the time has come for that,
so let us do nothing.


2120
04:13:57.130 --> 04:14:00.842
Let us go,
let us do as we're asked.”


2121
04:14:00.925 --> 04:14:03.970
He thinks the Jews expiated
the death of Christ?


2122
04:14:10.351 --> 04:14:13.938
He doesn't think so,
or even that Christ sought revenge.


2123
04:14:14.022 --> 04:14:17.525
He didn't say that.
The rabbi said it.


2124
04:14:20.653 --> 04:14:23.531
It was God's will, that's all!

2125
04:14:39.088 --> 04:14:41.466
- What'd she say?
- So Pilate washed his hands


2126
04:14:41.549 --> 04:14:46.638
and said, “Christ is innocent,”
he sent Barabbas.


2127
04:14:46.721 --> 04:14:48.806
But the Jews cried out,

2128
04:14:48.890 --> 04:14:51.893
“Let his blood fall on our heads.”

2129
04:14:54.854 --> 04:14:56.981
That's all. Now you know!

2130
04:16:21.065 --> 04:16:24.569
<i>Was the road between Chelmno,
the village</i>


2131
04:16:24.652 --> 04:16:26.738
<i>and the woods where the pits were,</i>

2132
04:16:26.821 --> 04:16:29.323
<i>was it asphalted as it is now?</i>

2133
04:16:45.423 --> 04:16:50.178
<i>The road was narrower then,
but it was asphalted.</i>


2134
04:16:59.771 --> 04:17:03.524
<i>How many feet
were the pits from the road?</i>


2135
04:17:28.216 --> 04:17:32.386
<i>They were around 1,600 feet,</i>

2136
04:17:32.470 --> 04:17:35.765
<i>maybe 1,900 or 2,200 feet away.</i>

2137
04:17:36.891 --> 04:17:41.395
<i>So even from the road,
you couldn't see them.</i>


2138
04:17:55.243 --> 04:17:57.745
How fast did the vans go?

2139
04:18:01.040 --> 04:18:04.252
PAN FALBORSKI

2140
04:18:04.585 --> 04:18:09.298
At moderate speed, kind of slow.

2141
04:18:27.108 --> 04:18:28.609
It was a calculated speed

2142
04:18:28.693 --> 04:18:34.073
because they had to kill
the people inside on the way.


2143
04:18:34.156 --> 04:18:35.950
When they went too fast,

2144
04:18:36.033 --> 04:18:40.454
the people weren't quite dead
on arrival in the woods.


2145
04:18:40.705 --> 04:18:47.128
By going slower, they had time
to kill the people inside.


2146
04:18:48.170 --> 04:18:52.425
Once a van skidded on a curve.

2147
04:19:05.146 --> 04:19:07.982
<i>Half an hour later, I arrived</i>

2148
04:19:08.065 --> 04:19:11.444
<i>at the hut of a forest warden
named Senajak.</i>


2149
04:19:22.622 --> 04:19:26.584
<i>He told me, “Too bad you were late.</i>

2150
04:19:26.667 --> 04:19:29.253
<i>You could have seen a van that skidded.</i>

2151
04:19:29.337 --> 04:19:32.632
<i>The rear of the van opened,</i>

2152
04:19:33.007 --> 04:19:35.843
<i>and the Jews fell out on the road.</i>

2153
04:19:38.930 --> 04:19:40.848
<i>They were still alive.</i>

2154
04:19:46.812 --> 04:19:52.360
<i>Seeing those Jews crawling,
a Gestapo man</i>


2155
04:19:52.443 --> 04:19:56.989
<i>took out his revolver and shot them.</i>

2156
04:20:09.126 --> 04:20:11.462
<i>He finished them all off.</i>

2157
04:20:13.130 --> 04:20:18.219
<i>Then they brought Jews
who were working in the woods.</i>


2158
04:20:22.181 --> 04:20:25.601
<i>They righted the van</i>

2159
04:20:26.310 --> 04:20:29.563
<i>and put the bodies back inside.”</i>

2160
04:20:39.073 --> 04:20:41.075
<i>This was the road</i>

2161
04:20:42.118 --> 04:20:47.081
<i>the gas vans used.</i>

2162
04:20:48.916 --> 04:20:52.545
<i>There were 80 people in each van.</i>

2163
04:20:57.758 --> 04:21:01.012
<i>When they arrived, the SS said,</i>

2164
04:21:01.095 --> 04:21:03.139
<i>“Open the doors!”</i>

2165
04:21:03.848 --> 04:21:09.145
<i>We opened them.
The bodies tumbled right out.</i>


2166
04:21:10.604 --> 04:21:13.149
<i>An SS man said, “2 men inside!”</i>

2167
04:21:13.524 --> 04:21:19.238
<i>These 2 men worked at the ovens.
They were experienced.</i>


2168
04:21:20.448 --> 04:21:22.867
<i>Another SS man screamed,</i>

2169
04:21:22.950 --> 04:21:28.122
<i>“Hurry up!
The other van's coming!”</i>


2170
04:21:28.998 --> 04:21:34.754
<i>We worked until
the whole shipment was burned.</i>


2171
04:21:39.508 --> 04:21:43.888
<i>That's how it went, all daylong.
So it went.</i>


2172
04:22:13.876 --> 04:22:18.339
<i>I remember
that once they were still alive.</i>


2173
04:22:21.425 --> 04:22:24.220
<i>The ovens were full,</i>

2174
04:22:26.388 --> 04:22:29.725
<i>and the people lay on the ground.</i>

2175
04:22:30.392 --> 04:22:33.354
<i>They were all moving,</i>

2176
04:22:33.437 --> 04:22:36.148
<i>they were coming back to life,</i>

2177
04:22:39.360 --> 04:22:42.738
<i>and when they were thrown
into the ovens,</i>


2178
04:22:42.822 --> 04:22:44.448
<i>they were all conscious. Alive.</i>

2179
04:22:44.532 --> 04:22:48.035
<i>They could feel the fire burn them.</i>

2180
04:23:09.640 --> 04:23:15.020
<i>When we built the ovens,
I wondered what they were for.</i>


2181
04:23:18.399 --> 04:23:20.776
<i>An SS man told me,</i>

2182
04:23:21.068 --> 04:23:25.948
<i>“To make charcoal.
For laundry irons.”</i>


2183
04:23:26.907 --> 04:23:29.410
<i>That's what he told me.
I didn't know.</i>


2184
04:23:32.580 --> 04:23:35.624
<i>When the ovens were completed,</i>

2185
04:23:37.751 --> 04:23:40.880
<i>the logs put in</i>

2186
04:23:40.963 --> 04:23:44.758
<i>and the gasoline poured on and lighted,</i>

2187
04:23:46.594 --> 04:23:49.597
<i>and when the first gas van arrived,</i>

2188
04:23:50.055 --> 04:23:55.102
<i>then we knew why the ovens were built.</i>

2189
04:24:04.862 --> 04:24:08.324
<i>When I saw all
that, it didn't affect me.</i>

2190
04:24:09.491 --> 04:24:14.205
<i>Neither did the 2nd or 3rd shipment.</i>

2191
04:24:17.124 --> 04:24:20.294
<i>I was only 13,</i>

2192
04:24:20.628 --> 04:24:24.548
<i>and all I'd ever seen until then</i>

2193
04:24:24.632 --> 04:24:28.135
<i>were dead bodies.</i>

2194
04:24:32.723 --> 04:24:34.892
Maybe I didn't understand.

2195
04:24:35.726 --> 04:24:41.315
Maybe if I'd been older
I'd have understood,


2196
04:24:41.398 --> 04:24:43.317
but the fact is, I didn't.

2197
04:24:43.525 --> 04:24:47.404
I'd never seen anything else.

2198
04:24:48.322 --> 04:24:53.077
In the ghetto, I saw...
in the ghetto in Lodz,


2199
04:24:53.160 --> 04:24:57.665
that as soon as anyone took a step,
he fell dead.


2200
04:24:57.998 --> 04:25:02.002
I thought that was
the way things had to be.


2201
04:25:02.378 --> 04:25:03.921
It was normal.

2202
04:25:04.004 --> 04:25:06.131
I'd walk the streets of Lodz,

2203
04:25:07.341 --> 04:25:11.845
maybe 100 yards,
and there'd be 200 bodies.


2204
04:25:14.848 --> 04:25:16.684
People were hungry.

2205
04:25:16.767 --> 04:25:20.229
They went into the street
and they fell, they fell...


2206
04:25:21.438 --> 04:25:24.358
Sons took their fathers' bread,

2207
04:25:24.441 --> 04:25:27.653
fathers took their sons'.

2208
04:25:27.736 --> 04:25:31.073
Everyone wanted to stay alive.

2209
04:25:33.200 --> 04:25:36.287
So when I came here, to Chelmno,

2210
04:25:36.787 --> 04:25:38.622
I was already...

2211
04:25:39.373 --> 04:25:42.376
I didn't care about anything.

2212
04:25:42.960 --> 04:25:48.424
I thought, if I survive,

2213
04:25:48.507 --> 04:25:50.718
I just want one thing:

2214
04:25:52.261 --> 04:25:54.596
5 loaves of bread to eat.

2215
04:25:54.680 --> 04:25:56.265
That's all.

2216
04:25:56.515 --> 04:25:59.059
That's what I thought.

2217
04:25:59.143 --> 04:26:00.936
But I dreamed, too,

2218
04:26:01.020 --> 04:26:04.440
that if I survived,
I'd be the only one left in the world,


2219
04:26:04.523 --> 04:26:07.192
not another soul. Just me. One.

2220
04:26:13.657 --> 04:26:17.745
<i>Only me left in the world,
if I get out of here.</i>


2221
04:26:34.511 --> 04:26:37.264
THE RUHR

2222
04:26:38.766 --> 04:26:43.979
<i>“Geheime Reichssache, ”
secret Reich business.</i>


2223
04:26:46.023 --> 04:26:49.610
<i>“Berlin, June 5, 1942.</i>

2224
04:26:52.613 --> 04:26:57.743
<i>Changes to be made
to special vehicles now in service</i>


2225
04:26:57.951 --> 04:27:00.287
<i>at Kulmhof (Chelmno)</i>

2226
04:27:00.662 --> 04:27:02.664
<i>and to those now being built.</i>

2227
04:27:08.170 --> 04:27:11.090
<i>Since December 1941,</i>

2228
04:27:11.965 --> 04:27:18.389
<i>97,000 have been processed
(verarbeitet in German)</i>


2229
04:27:19.306 --> 04:27:23.227
<i>by the 3 vehicles in service,
with no major incident.</i>


2230
04:27:25.521 --> 04:27:30.067
<i>In light of observations
made so far, however,</i>


2231
04:27:30.150 --> 04:27:33.445
<i>the following technical changes
are needed:</i>


2232
04:27:34.655 --> 04:27:35.989
<i>First,</i>

2233
04:27:36.865 --> 04:27:42.413
<i>the van's normal load
is usually 9 to 10 per square yard.</i>


2234
04:27:44.832 --> 04:27:48.836
<i>In Saurer vehicles,
which are very spacious,</i>


2235
04:27:50.003 --> 04:27:53.632
<i>maximum use of space is impossible,</i>

2236
04:27:54.341 --> 04:27:57.511
<i>not because of any possible overload,</i>

2237
04:27:58.846 --> 04:28:02.349
<i>but because loading to full capacity</i>

2238
04:28:02.433 --> 04:28:06.103
<i>would affect the vehicle's stability.</i>

2239
04:28:07.771 --> 04:28:11.984
<i>So reduction of the load space
seems necessary.</i>


2240
04:28:14.236 --> 04:28:17.656
<i>It must absolutely
be reduced by a yard,</i>


2241
04:28:17.739 --> 04:28:22.286
<i>instead of trying to solve the problem,
as hitherto,</i>


2242
04:28:22.369 --> 04:28:25.914
<i>by reducing the number
of pieces loaded.</i>


2243
04:28:29.126 --> 04:28:34.590
<i>Besides, this extends the operating time,</i>

2244
04:28:36.258 --> 04:28:40.637
<i>as the empty void must also
be filled with carbon monoxide.</i>


2245
04:28:42.389 --> 04:28:46.810
<i>On the other hand,
if the load space is reduced</i>


2246
04:28:47.436 --> 04:28:50.439
<i>and the vehicle is packed solid,</i>

2247
04:28:51.231 --> 04:28:55.486
<i>the operating time can be
considerably shortened.</i>


2248
04:28:56.945 --> 04:29:00.699
<i>The manufacturers told us
during a discussion,</i>


2249
04:29:01.283 --> 04:29:05.037
<i>that reducing the size
of the van's rear</i>


2250
04:29:05.621 --> 04:29:08.165
<i>would throw it badly off balance.</i>

2251
04:29:09.249 --> 04:29:13.128
<i>The front axle, they claim,
would be overloaded.</i>


2252
04:29:16.298 --> 04:29:21.970
<i>In fact, the balance
is automatically restored</i>


2253
04:29:23.180 --> 04:29:26.266
<i>because the merchandise aboard</i>

2254
04:29:27.434 --> 04:29:31.021
<i>displays, during the operation,</i>

2255
04:29:31.104 --> 04:29:35.442
<i>a natural tendency
to rush to the rear doors,</i>


2256
04:29:36.652 --> 04:29:41.698
<i>and are mainly found lying there
at the end of the operation.</i>


2257
04:29:44.284 --> 04:29:49.248
<i>So the front axle is not overloaded.</i>

2258
04:29:54.378 --> 04:29:55.963
<i>Secondly:</i>

2259
04:29:58.215 --> 04:30:03.887
<i>The lighting must be
better protected than now.</i>


2260
04:30:06.139 --> 04:30:09.434
<i>The lamps must be enclosed
in a steel grid</i>


2261
04:30:09.518 --> 04:30:12.437
<i>to prevent their being damaged.</i>

2262
04:30:14.523 --> 04:30:17.192
<i>Lights could be eliminated,</i>

2263
04:30:17.276 --> 04:30:20.821
<i>since they apparently are never used.</i>

2264
04:30:22.864 --> 04:30:27.119
<i>However, it has been observed</i>

2265
04:30:27.202 --> 04:30:29.746
<i>that when the doors are shut,</i>

2266
04:30:30.747 --> 04:30:36.753
<i>the load always
presses hard against them</i>


2267
04:30:36.837 --> 04:30:39.172
<i>(against the doors)</i>

2268
04:30:39.256 --> 04:30:41.967
<i>as soon as darkness sets in.</i>

2269
04:30:42.884 --> 04:30:46.179
<i>This is because the load</i>

2270
04:30:46.805 --> 04:30:49.850
<i>naturally rushes toward the light</i>

2271
04:30:51.393 --> 04:30:53.353
<i>when darkness sets in,</i>

2272
04:30:54.688 --> 04:30:57.816
<i>which makes
closing the doors difficult.</i>


2273
04:31:00.235 --> 04:31:05.907
<i>Also, because
of the alarming nature of darkness,</i>


2274
04:31:07.242 --> 04:31:13.081
<i>screaming always occurs
when the doors are closed.</i>


2275
04:31:15.375 --> 04:31:18.545
<i>It would therefore be useful
to light the lamp</i>


2276
04:31:19.546 --> 04:31:23.216
<i>before and during
the first moments of the operation.</i>


2277
04:31:26.303 --> 04:31:27.804
<i>Third:</i>

2278
04:31:30.057 --> 04:31:32.851
<i>For easy cleaning of the vehicle,</i>

2279
04:31:33.727 --> 04:31:38.774
<i>there must be a sealed drain
in the middle of the ﬂoor.</i>


2280
04:31:40.567 --> 04:31:45.947
<i>The drainage hole's cover,

2281
04:31:46.948 --> 04:31:49.534
<i>would be equipped with a slanting trap,</i>

2282
04:31:50.452 --> 04:31:53.538
<i>so that ﬂuid liquids</i>

2283
04:31:57.000 --> 04:32:00.253
<i>can drain off during the operation.</i>

2284
04:32:05.676 --> 04:32:07.552
<i>During cleaning,</i>

2285
04:32:07.761 --> 04:32:12.432
<i>the drain can be used
to evacuate large pieces of din'.</i>


2286
04:32:22.484 --> 04:32:25.612
<i>The aforementioned technical changes</i>

2287
04:32:25.696 --> 04:32:28.281
<i>are to be made
to vehicles in service</i>


2288
04:32:28.365 --> 04:32:32.035
<i>only when they come in for repairs.</i>

2289
04:32:34.621 --> 04:32:38.125
<i>As for the 10 vehicles
ordered from Saurer,</i>


2290
04:32:41.795 --> 04:32:47.718
<i>they must be equipped
with all innovations and changes</i>


2291
04:32:48.802 --> 04:32:52.097
<i>shown by use
and experience to be necessary.</i>


2292
04:32:54.975 --> 04:32:59.604
<i>Submitted for decision
to Gruppenleiter II D,</i>


2293
04:32:59.688 --> 04:33:04.151
<i>SS
-Obersturmbannfuhrer Walter Rauff.</i>

2294
04:33:06.069 --> 04:33:08.697
<i>Signed Just.”</i>

2295
04:33:19.040 --> 04:33:22.002
END OF THE FIRST ERA